{"type":"text","timestamp":1773436089901,"sessionID":"ses_316fcb79fffeLVMPL0QpkiSz53","part":{"id":"prt_ce906b11c0010oUCF63l0foIjs","sessionID":"ses_316fcb79fffeLVMPL0QpkiSz53","messageID":"msg_ce906a469001wegJWMdKznatJ2","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nAdd a TDD verification step to the build pipeline in the wombo-combo AI agent orchestration system. This involves running tests (`bun test`), checking that new files have corresponding test files (via existing test-detection module), reporting results, and integrating with the existing verify command with `--skip-tests` and `--strict-tdd` flags. The verification should be non-blocking by default (warn on missing tests) with `--strict-tdd` to make it blocking.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Follow the feature spec from `tdd-verification-step` task description\n- Steps: 1) Run `bun test` and capture exit code + output, 2) Call test-detection to check new files have tests, 3) Report results, 4) Integrate with verify command adding `--skip-tests` flag, 5) In agent workflow: verification runs after agent commits, before marking task done\n- Non-blocking by default (warn on missing tests), `--strict-tdd` flag makes it blocking\n- Use conventional commits with scope `tdd-verification-step`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `undefined`\n- Use Bun APIs, TypeScript strict mode, ESM only, `.js` extensions in imports\n- Run `bun run build` to verify everything works at the end\n- Use `portless run` when starting any server\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- The project already has a `TddConfig` interface in `src/config.ts` with `enabled` and `testCommand` fields, and a `tdd` section in `DEFAULT_CONFIG`\n- The project already has `src/lib/test-detection.ts` which handles git diff analysis, test file matching, and coverage reporting — this is the \"tdd-test-detection\" module referenced in the spec\n- `runFullVerification` in `src/lib/verifier.ts` is the main verification pipeline function called by `handleBuildVerification` in `launch.ts` — this is where TDD verification needs to be integrated\n- The `FullVerificationResult` type already had `build` + `browser` fields; I added `tdd` as a third field\n- `runFullVerification` signature was extended with an optional `opts?: FullVerificationOptions` parameter so existing callers (launch.ts line 302) still compile without changes\n- The schema registry in `src/lib/schema.ts` needs to be updated for `--skip-tests` and `--strict-tdd` flags on the `verify` command\n- tsconfig only includes `src/**/*.ts` — tests in `tests/` are excluded from typecheck\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed:\n1. **Created `src/lib/test-runner.ts`** — Runs test commands, captures exit code/stdout/stderr, parses test counts from bun/jest output formats, extracts error summaries\n2. **Created `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts`** — Orchestrates test running + test detection, produces `TddVerificationResult` with strict/warn modes, includes text rendering and error summary extraction\n3. **Updated `src/lib/verifier.ts`** — Added `TddVerificationResult` to `FullVerificationResult`, added `FullVerificationOptions` type, integrated TDD verification as step 3 in `runFullVerification`, combined TDD errors with build/browser errors\n4. **Commits made:** 2 commits on branch `feature/tdd-verification-step`\n\n### In Progress:\n5. **Updating `src/config.ts`** — Added `strictTdd: boolean` and `testTimeout: number` fields to `TddConfig` interface, but **there's a build error**: the `DEFAULT_CONFIG` object is missing the new fields (`strictTdd`, `testTimeout`). This needs to be fixed immediately — add `strictTdd: false` and `testTimeout: 120_000` to the `tdd` section of `DEFAULT_CONFIG` (around line 217-219).\n\n### Remaining TODO:\n6. **Update `src/commands/verify.ts`** — Add `skipTests` and `strictTdd` options to `VerifyCommandOptions`, pass them through to `runFullVerification`, report TDD results\n7. **Update `src/index.ts`** — Parse `--skip-tests` and `--strict-tdd` CLI flags in `parseArgs`, add to `CLIArgs` interface, wire them to the verify command call and launch command\n8. **Update `src/lib/schema.ts`** — Add `--skip-tests` and `--strict-tdd` flag definitions to the verify command schema entry (around line 196)\n9. **Update `src/commands/launch.ts`** — The `handleBuildVerification` function calls `runFullVerification` on line 302 — it should report TDD results (similar to how browser results are reported on lines 306-314), and potentially pass through TDD options\n10. **Run `bun run build`** to verify everything compiles\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Created:\n- `src/lib/test-runner.ts` — Test command runner with output parsing\n- `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts` — TDD verification orchestrator\n\n### Modified (changes committed):\n- `src/lib/verifier.ts` — Added TDD step to full verification pipeline\n\n### Modified (changes in progress, NOT committed, has LSP error):\n- `src/config.ts` — Added `strictTdd` and `testTimeout` to `TddConfig` interface; **NEEDS FIX**: add defaults to `DEFAULT_CONFIG.tdd` object (around line 217)\n\n### Need modification:\n- `src/commands/verify.ts` — Add `--skip-tests`/`--strict-tdd` options\n- `src/index.ts` — Parse new CLI flags, wire to verify/launch commands\n- `src/lib/schema.ts` — Register new flags in command schema (verify command at ~line 189)\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Report TDD results in `handleBuildVerification`\n\n### Reference files (read, not modified):\n- `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — Existing test detection module (used by tdd-verifier.ts)\n- `src/lib/browser-verifier.ts` — Pattern reference for how browser verification was integrated\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Already has TDD prompt generation (lines 166-184)\n- `package.json` — Build script: `bun build src/index.ts --outdir dist --target node`\n- `tsconfig.json` — Strict mode, only includes `src/**/*.ts`\n- `AGENTS.md` — Project conventions and constraints","time":{"start":1773436089900,"end":1773436089900}}}
